  "prompt": "Is 2Mbps a good speed for browsing and downloading limited things over broadband? Should I choose 4Mbps?",
  "response": "A speed of 2 Mbps can handle basic browsing and limited downloading, such as checking emails, streaming music, and accessing standard websites. However, it may struggle with more data-intensive activities, such as streaming videos in anything other than low resolution, online gaming, or downloading larger files.\n\nIf your usage includes more than just basic browsing\u2014like streaming videos in higher quality, multiple devices connected at the same time, or more substantial downloads\u2014then upgrading to 4 Mbps would provide a better experience. It would offer more bandwidth to accommodate these activities, potentially reducing buffering and improving overall performance. \n\nUltimately, your choice should depend on the specific activities you plan to do online and how many devices will be using the connection simultaneously. If budget allows and your usage is more than basic, opting for 4 Mbps is a wise choice.",
